---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro"

import Hero from "../components/Hero.astro"
import TechnicalDivider from "../components/TechnicalDivider.astro"
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | Joshua Jadulco"
  description="Technical profile - Full Stack Web Developer with expertise in Laravel, Vue, and modern web technologies"
>
  <main class="wrapper stack gap-12">
    <section class="stack gap-8">
      <Hero
        title="ABOUT_PROFILE"
        tagline="Technical profile - Background, experience, and technology stack analysis"
        align="start"
      />

      <div class="about-content stack gap-12">
        <div class="content-card">
          <TechnicalDivider title="BACKGROUND_PROFILE" />
          <div class="card-body stack gap-4">
            <p>
              I am a results-driven Senior Laravel Developer with over 5 years of experience architecting and delivering
              scalable web applications for enterprise clients. Throughout my career, I specialized in full-stack Laravel development
              and built deep expertise in the entire Laravel ecosystem, including Eloquent ORM, Service Container,
              Laravel Queues, Middleware pipelines, and advanced design patterns. I have a proven track record of
              leading cross-functional teams, optimizing application performance, and implementing robust
              CI/CD pipelines that reduced deployment time by 40% and significantly improved overall code quality.
            </p>
            <p>
              In my previous roles, I architected and developed enterprise-grade Laravel applications utilizing advanced OOP design
              patterns including Repository, Factory, Observer, and Strategy patterns. I leveraged Laravel's
              Eloquent ORM with complex relationships, eager loading, and query optimization to handle enterprise-level data
              models with millions of records. I implemented Service Container dependency injection, custom Service Providers, and
              Middleware pipelines to create scalable application architectures. I also utilized Laravel Queues with
              Redis and database drivers for high-volume background job processing, and configured Laravel Horizon for real-time
              queue monitoring and management.
            </p>
            <p>
              I have extensive hands-on experience with the complete Laravel ecosystem. I built custom admin dashboards using Laravel Nova,
              implemented full-text search with Laravel Scout integrated with Algolia and Meilisearch, and developed OAuth authentication
              systems using Laravel Socialite with multiple providers including Google, GitHub, and Microsoft. I secured API endpoints
              using Laravel Sanctum for token-based authentication. Additionally, I optimized application performance through advanced query optimization,
              Redis caching strategies, OPcache configuration, database indexing, and Laravel's caching layer with tags and atomic locks.
              I designed and implemented comprehensive RESTful APIs using Laravel's API resources, versioning strategies,
              rate limiting, and industry-standard architecture patterns.
            </p>
            <p>
              I am a strong advocate for Test Driven Development (TDD) and Behavior Driven Development (BDD). In my projects,
              I implemented comprehensive testing strategies using PHPUnit, Pest, and Laravel Dusk, achieving 90%+ code coverage across
              multiple enterprise applications. I wrote extensive unit tests, feature tests, and browser tests utilizing mocking,
              test doubles, and database transactions for isolated testing. I integrated automated testing into CI/CD pipelines with GitHub Actions,
              which enabled continuous deployment workflows and caught regressions before they reached production. I consistently utilized Laravel's
              testing helpers, factories, seeders, and HTTP testing to accelerate test development and maintain high quality standards.
            </p>
            <p>
              I led multiple DevOps initiatives using Docker and Docker Compose to create consistent, containerized Laravel
              environments with PHP-FPM, Nginx, Redis, and MySQL. I automated CI/CD pipelines for
              testing, building, and deploying to staging and production environments, which streamlined our release process.
              I managed Linux server infrastructure running Ubuntu and Debian, implementing deployment
              automation, log rotation, SSL certificate management, and environment provisioning using Ansible
              and Bash scripting. I also leveraged AWS services including EC2, S3, RDS, CloudFront, and
              Elastic Load Balancing to build scalable cloud infrastructure with high availability and fault tolerance.
            </p>
            <p>
              I have practiced Agile and Scrum methodologies throughout my career, serving as both a team lead and senior developer. I facilitated
              sprint planning sessions, daily standups, sprint reviews, and retrospectives for teams of up to 8 developers. I created detailed user
              stories with clear acceptance criteria and definition of done, managed sprint backlogs with velocity
              tracking, and mentored junior developers in Laravel best practices, design patterns, and coding standards.
              I collaborated closely with stakeholders, product managers, and UX designers to translate business
              requirements into technical specifications and deliverables. I utilized Jira, Confluence, and
              Azure DevOps for project tracking, documentation, and seamless team collaboration.
            </p>
            <p>
              I have extensive experience with various enterprise SDLC methodologies, including Waterfall for
              regulated industries and hybrid Agile-Waterfall approaches for complex projects. I performed requirements gathering sessions with clients,
              created comprehensive technical specification documentation, designed system architectures, and built database schemas
              for mission-critical enterprise applications. I conducted thorough code reviews, implemented coding standards across development teams,
              and maintained detailed technical documentation for API endpoints, deployment procedures,
              and system architecture. I also provided ongoing maintenance, security updates, and performance
              optimization for production Laravel applications successfully serving thousands of concurrent users.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
